Investment South Africa (ISA) will, on Tuesday, sign a memorandum of understanding (MoU) with Thailand&rsquo;s investment and business source Thailand Board of Investment to advance trade between the two countries. &ldquo;The MoU, which will be signed in Bangkok, Thailand, is aimed at promoting and facilitating cooperation between the two countries on investments in the automotive, agroprocessing and electronics sectors,&rdquo; ISA acting head Yunus Hoosen said in a statement. &nbsp; He added that officials from the Richards Bay Industrial Development Zone (RBIDZ) will be part of a delegation meeting with Thai companies to attract Thai automotive component manufacturers to invest in the RBIDZ. &nbsp; &ldquo;We are optimistic that the implementation of the MoU will see Thai investors setting up manufacturing plants in South Africa, which will result in job creation,&rdquo; Hoosen said. Trade between South Africa and Thailand for the first three quarters of 2016 reached R29.9-billion, a 24.3% year-on-year increase.